# HTML in Twig — museothyssen

When writing markup with **Tailwind v4** in Twig:

- **Minimal nodes**: stack utilities on the needed element; do not duplicate trees only for breakpoints.
- **Semantics**: `article`, `section`, `nav`, `header`, `figure`, `button` vs clickable `div`.
- **Drupal**: use `{{ attributes }}` / `attributes.addClass()` on the SDC root element.
- **Attribute order** (recommended): `id` → `href`/`type`/`aria-*` → `class` → `data-*`.

## Single responsive tree

### ❌ Incorrect: duplicated desktop/mobile markup

```twig
<div class="hidden md:block">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">{{ title }}</h2>
</div>
<div class="block md:hidden">
  <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">{{ title }}</h2>
</div>
```

### ✅ Correct: same tags, responsive classes

```twig
<h2 class="text-xl font-bold md:text-2xl">{{ title }}</h2>
```

## Fewer wrappers

### ❌ Incorrect

```twig
<div class="wrapper">
  <div class="inner">
    <p class="p-4 bg-white rounded-lg">{{ text }}</p>
  </div>
</div>
```

### ✅ Correct

```twig
<p class="p-4 bg-white rounded-lg">{{ text }}</p>
```

## Accessibility in SDC

- Real buttons: `<button type="button">`, not `<div onclick>`.
- Links: `<a href="...">` with visible text; reusable CTA → `{% include 'museothyssen:action_link' %}`.
- Expandable state: `aria-expanded`, `aria-controls`, `hidden` on the panel (see `hello.twig`).
- Images: `canvas:image` with required `alt` in props; Media render arrays at runtime.

## Classes on the SDC root

```twig
<div{{ attributes.addClass(
  'museothyssen-hello',
  'rounded-2xl border border-slate-200/80 bg-white p-6',
  'shadow-sm ring-1 ring-slate-900/5',
) }}>
```

BEM prefix `museothyssen-{component}__element` for CSS/JS hooks (`[data-hello-toggle]`, `.museothyssen-hello__subtitle`).

## Composition

Include other SDCs with the theme namespace:

```twig
{% include 'museothyssen:action_link' with {
  attributes: create_attribute({}),
  url: link_url,
  label: link_label,
} only %}
```
